# Voiceover (Google Cloud Text-to-Speech)
# Used by: npm run docs:voiceover, npm run docs:render
# Docs: https://docs.cloud.google.com/text-to-speech/docs/create-audio-text-client-libraries

# Option A — Service account JSON (CI/CD or when you have a key file)
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/absolute/path/to/your-service-account.json

# Option B — Local dev without .env: use gcloud CLI (no key file needed)
#   1. Install: https://cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/install
#   2. gcloud init
#   3. gcloud auth application-default login
# The client library will then use these credentials automatically.
# (Cloud TTS does NOT support API keys.)
